article.headline: Lamar 64, Texas-San Antonio 57
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Justin Nabors had 16 points and 14 rebounds and Lamar held off UTSA 64-57 Saturday night. Anthony Miles had 19 points to lead the Cardinals (11-11, 3-4 Southland) and Charlie Harper added 10. Morris Smith IV led all scorers with 19 for UTSA (12-7, 2-4). No other Roadrunner was in double figures, but three players had nine points. Lamar outrebounded UTSA 38-26, but never led by more than eight points and the game was still close in the final minute. Lamar led 59-57 after Demarco Stepter scored for the Roadrunners with 25 seconds to play. Miles made the first of two free throws, Coy Custer scored off Miles' miss on the second one, and Miles later made two more free throws for the final margin.
